{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PD8FB11vbX2S31NW5cVdWE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll provide a comprehensive summary of the codebase:\n\nProject Overview:\n- Name: Spring PetClinic\n- Type: Spring Boot Web Application\n- Version: 3.5.0-SNAPSHOT\n- Java Version: 17\n- Build Tool: Maven (with Gradle support)\n\nKey Features:\n1. Web Framework: Spring Boot\n2. ORM: Spring Data JPA\n3. Database Support: \n   - H2 (default)\n   - MySQL\n   - PostgreSQL\n4. Template Engine: Thymeleaf\n5. Internationalization: Supports multiple languages (en, es, de, fa, ko, pt, ru, tr)\n\nMain Modules:\n1. Owners Management\n2. Pets Management\n3. Veterinarians Management\n4. Visits Tracking\n\nProject Structure:\n- src/main/java: Main application source code\n- src/main/resources: Configuration, templates, static resources\n- src/test/java: Unit and integration tests\n- k8s: Kubernetes deployment configurations\n- docker-compose.yml: Docker Compose configuration\n\nKey Configuration Files:\n1. application.properties\n   - Default database: H2\n   - Thymeleaf configuration\n   - JPA settings\n   - Internationalization\n   - Actuator endpoint exposure\n\n2. Dockerfile\n   - Uses maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble base image\n   - Installs additional tools like uv, Python\n   - Sets up environment for running the application\n   - Copies project files\n   - Default command: `mvn clean spring-boot:run`\n\n3. docker-compose.yml and k8s/*.yml: Provide container and Kubernetes deployment configurations\n\nImportant Java Classes:\n1. PetClinicApplication.java: Main application entry point\n2. Controllers: \n   - OwnerController\n   - PetController\n   - VetController\n   - WelcomeController\n3. Repositories:\n   - OwnerRepository\n   - PetTypeRepository\n   - VetRepository\n\nTest Coverage:\n- Unit Tests for Controllers, Models\n- Integration Tests for different database configurations\n- JMeter test plan included\n\nBuild and Deployment Options:\n- Maven\n- Gradle\n- Docker\n- Kubernetes\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the codebase?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"86feb03e-859a-478b-a600-b9ecbd92d7df"}
