{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01H4SFg3FYoamuEqjD9pq46L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that `/owners/{ownerId}` from `OwnerResource` is not matching. This happens because in JAX-RS, `@PathParam` integer types won't match string paths. Actually `@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId` should convert. But the issue might be that `PetResource` with `@Path(\"/owners/{ownerId}\")` takes precedence.\n\nWait, let me re-examine. The `OwnerResource` is `@Path(\"/owners\")` and within it:\n- `@GET @Path(\"/find\")` -> `/owners/find` \n- `@GET @Path(\"/{ownerId}\")` -> `/owners/{ownerId}`\n\nThese should work. Let me check if the template injection is failing. In Quarkus, `@Inject Template xxx` requires that the template file name matches `xxx.html` or `xxx.txt`. Let me verify:\n\n- `findOwners` template -> `src/main/resources/templates/findOwners.html` - correct\n- `createOrUpdateOwnerForm` template -> `src/main/resources/templates/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html` - correct\n- `ownersList` template -> should be `ownersList.html` - correct\n- `ownerDetails` template -> should be `ownerDetails.html` - correct\n\nLet me add more debugging:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":522,"cache_read_input_tokens":147068,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":522,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":403},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"615db9fe-dad6-4e71-afd5-b909534f9ca0"}
