{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EAbust9VfhLJmsBXywo7j4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owners</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <table id=\"owners\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→      <tr>\n     8→        <th style=\"width: 150px;\">Name</th>\n     9→        <th style=\"width: 200px;\">Address</th>\n    10→        <th>City</th>\n    11→        <th style=\"width: 120px\">Telephone</th>\n    12→        <th>Pets</th>\n    13→      </tr>\n    14→    </thead>\n    15→    <tbody>\n    16→      {#for owner in listOwners}\n    17→      <tr>\n    18→        <td>\n    19→          <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}\">{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</a>\n    20→        </td>\n    21→        <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    22→        <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→        <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    24→        <td>\n    25→          {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    26→            {pet.name}{#if !isLast}, {/if}\n    27→          {/for}\n    28→        </td>\n    29→      </tr>\n    30→      {/for}\n    31→    </tbody>\n    32→  </table>\n    33→\n    34→  <nav aria-label=\"Page navigation\">\n    35→    <ul class=\"pagination\">\n    36→      <li class=\"page-item {#if currentPage == 1}disabled{/if}\">\n    37→        <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/owners?page={currentPage - 1}&lastName=\">Previous</a>\n    38→      </li>\n    39→      {#for i in totalPages}\n    40→      <li class=\"page-item {#if currentPage == i + 1}active{/if}\">\n    41→        <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/owners?page={i + 1}&lastName=\">{i + 1}</a>\n    42→      </li>\n    43→      {/for}\n    44→      <li class=\"page-item {#if currentPage == totalPages}disabled{/if}\">\n    45→        <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/owners?page={currentPage + 1}&lastName=\">Next</a>\n    46→      </li>\n    47→    </ul>\n    48→  </nav>\n    49→{/body}\n    50→{/include}\n    51→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"b8917d78-bf72-4245-99e3-41e56385b1e9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019mXnLPod94uT8a1BGVtaF2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Veterinarians</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <table id=\"vets\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→      <tr>\n     8→        <th>Name</th>\n     9→        <th>Specialties</th>\n    10→      </tr>\n    11→    </thead>\n    12→    <tbody>\n    13→      {#for vet in listVets}\n    14→      <tr>\n    15→        <td>{vet.firstName} {vet.lastName}</td>\n    16→        <td>\n    17→          {#if vet.nrOfSpecialties == 0}\n    18→            none\n    19→          {#else}\n    20→            {#for spec in vet.specialties}\n    21→              {spec.name}{#if !isLast} {/if}\n    22→            {/for}\n    23→          {/if}\n    24→        </td>\n    25→      </tr>\n    26→      {/for}\n    27→    </tbody>\n    28→  </table>\n    29→\n    30→  <nav aria-label=\"Page navigation\">\n    31→    <ul class=\"pagination\">\n    32→      <li class=\"page-item {#if currentPage == 1}disabled{/if}\">\n    33→        <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/vets.html?page={currentPage - 1}\">Previous</a>\n    34→      </li>\n    35→      {#for i in totalPages}\n    36→      <li class=\"page-item {#if currentPage == i + 1}active{/if}\">\n    37→        <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/vets.html?page={i + 1}\">{i + 1}</a>\n    38→      </li>\n    39→      {/for}\n    40→      <li class=\"page-item {#if currentPage == totalPages}disabled{/if}\">\n    41→        <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/vets.html?page={currentPage + 1}\">Next</a>\n    42→      </li>\n    43→    </ul>\n    44→  </nav>\n    45→{/body}\n    46→{/include}\n    47→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"21d35bb8-d61c-4613-b4eb-78bcfbd01c24"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LeyuQHQ6M1mCCsfo2AsLqw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include layout.html}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→  <h2>Owner Information</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <table class=\"table table-striped\" style=\"width:600px;\">\n     6→    <tr>\n     7→      <th>Name</th>\n     8→      <td><b>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</b></td>\n     9→    </tr>\n    10→    <tr>\n    11→      <th>Address</th>\n    12→      <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    13→    </tr>\n    14→    <tr>\n    15→      <th>City</th>\n    16→      <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    17→    </tr>\n    18→    <tr>\n    19→      <th>Telephone</th>\n    20→      <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    21→    </tr>\n    22→  </table>\n    23→\n    24→  <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/edit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Edit Owner</a>\n    25→  <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/new\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Add New Pet</a>\n    26→\n    27→  <br />\n    28→  <br />\n    29→  <br />\n    30→  <h2>Pets and Visits</h2>\n    31→\n    32→  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    33→    {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    34→    <tr>\n    35→      <td valign=\"top\">\n    36→        <dl class=\"dl-horizontal\">\n    37→          <dt>Name</dt>\n    38→          <dd>{pet.name}</dd>\n    39→          <dt>Birth Date</dt>\n    40→          <dd>{pet.birthDate}</dd>\n    41→          <dt>Type</dt>\n    42→          <dd>{pet.type}</dd>\n    43→        </dl>\n    44→      </td>\n    45→      <td valign=\"top\">\n    46→        <table class=\"table-condensed\">\n    47→          <thead>\n    48→            <tr>\n    49→              <th>Visit Date</th>\n    50→              <th>Description</th>\n    51→            </tr>\n    52→          </thead>\n    53→          {#for visit in pet.visits}\n    54→          <tr>\n    55→            <td>{visit.date}</td>\n    56→            <td>{visit.description}</td>\n    57→          </tr>\n    58→          {/for}\n    59→          <tr>\n    60→            <td>\n    61→              <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/visits/new\">Add Visit</a>\n    62→            </td>\n    63→          </tr>\n    64→        </table>\n    65→      </td>\n    66→      <td>\n    67→        <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/edit\">Edit Pet</a>\n    68→      </td>\n    69→    </tr>\n    70→    {/for}\n    71→  </table>\n    72→{/body}\n    73→{/include}\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"4aa0eed6-fb39-4752-affc-ed08144dfa96"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FixpdFsoSkLq8EDL3moP2o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to fix two issues in the templates:\n\n1. **`{#if !isLast}`** → In Qute, the iteration metadata uses `hasNext` (true if there are more elements). So `{#if !isLast}` should become `{#if hasNext}`.\n\n2. **`{#for i in totalPages}`** → In Qute, iterating over an integer creates a range from 1 to N (inclusive), so `i` starts at 1, not 0. Need to adjust the pagination logic accordingly.\n\nLet me also check how Qute handles integer iteration to be sure:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2753,"cache_read_input_tokens":30400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2753,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":213},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"3937c0f1-34fc-4272-aeb7-647441e97655"}
