{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EMURFU12wqSRVxbvUiz65v","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The root causes are clear:\n\n1. **findOwners.html line 11**: `Key \"noResults\" not found` - Qute's strict mode requires all keys in `{#if}` conditionals to exist in the data map. When `noResults` is not set, the template fails.\n\n2. **createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html line 5**: `Key \"errors\" not found` - Same issue. The `{#if errors}` check fails because `errors` was never added to the data map.\n\nIn Qute with strict mode, you need to either always provide the key or use the `??` (or-empty) operator. The fix is to use `{#if errors??}` or always pass the values. The cleanest fix is to use the Qute null-safe `??` operator in the templates.\n\nLet me also check what the owners list failure is about:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3535,"cache_read_input_tokens":56884,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3535,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":308},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86a09403-f8e6-4dd1-bd75-9998012ce328","uuid":"2f84635d-a6c8-45c7-94fe-b4726a9cc855"}
